body:
### Description
As a node operator I'd like to perform maintenance/updates on existing nodes which would restart the node and triggers this behaviour

### Acceptance Criteria
Restarting a node doesn't cause it to be non functional anymore ie it will resume peering and continue to import blocks

### Steps to Reproduce (Bug)
See attached zip files
1. Extract zip file
2. Start the network up as normal with ./run.sh
3. Give it a few mins for blocks to be created.
3. Run `docker stop quorum-test-network-member1_1`. Run a `docker ps` to find the name of the container 
4. Wait about a minute for it to stop
5. Run  `docker start quorum-test-network-member1_1` and follow the logs and metrics

Logs show  saving blocks and peer counts of 0, instead of importing blocks and peer count of 7 or so
